comments.body:
I am against adding a no-header parameter. Oftentimes, adding more parameters is adding complexity at the users' side that should be handled by the library. The above issue is an example for such a case.

My suggestion is to instead add another API to extract the data for a set of processes as proposed by @marcov here https://github.com/containers/psgo/issues/32. All the logic can be implemented in `psgo` and libpod only needs to pass a slice of pids.

@haircommander, if you like this proposal, we can extend psgo early next week and get everything into the next Podman release on time.
